      "content": "From a policy perspective, healthcare is a deeply contested issue with valid arguments on both sides. Proponents of universal healthcare view access to care as a fundamental human right, arguing that health is essential for human dignity and productivity. Conversely, critics often argue that government-run systems can become bureaucratic, inefficient, and stifle market-driven innovation. Ultimately, the \"reality\" depends on which underlying economic and ethical values a society prioritizes.",
